<headline>Special Weather Statement issued October 18 at 3:06AM EDT  by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg</headline>
<description>...INCREASED FIRE DANGER IN EFFECT FROM NOON EDT TODAY THROUGH
THIS AFTERNOON ACROSS PORTIONS OF NORTHEAST GEORGIA...
Despite cooler temperatures across the region today, very dry air
will lead to afternoon relative humidity values falling to 25
percent or less for several hours. A few wind gusts of 15 to 20
mph are possible as well. These conditions will combine with dry
brush and other fuels to increase fire danger across the area this
afternoon.
Please refer to your local burn permitting authorities on whether
you can burn today. If you do burn, use extreme caution since
fires can quickly get out of hand under these conditions.</description>
